If you generate ids like:<p><pre><code>    &lt;fixed width timestamp&gt;&lt;random data&gt;
</code></pre>
Your ids are guaranteed to be sorted chronologically until you start generating them at the same time. So as a hack to work around that they generate:<p><pre><code>    &lt;fixed width timestamp&gt;&lt;fuzzed random data&gt;
</code></pre>
Where the fuzz to the random data ensures that it&#x27;s sorted chronologically.
